{
  "texts": [
    "The resulting single-agent controller is then fixed and extended to the multi-agent case through a heuristic high-level controller (Sec.IV-B), which, despite being suboptimal, avoids the curse of dimensionality.",
    "This hierarchical decomposition alleviates the burden of multi-agent decision making while promoting specialization, modularity, and scalability.",
    "LEARNING AND DEPLOYMENT A.",
    "Learning the Low-Level Driving PolicyWe begin by training the low-level driving policy in a nominal environment comprising one herder, one target, and a single obstacle.",
    "The policy is parameterized by a neural network and trained using the actor-critic Proximal Policy Optimization (PPO) algorithm [24], suitable for continuous action spaces."
  ]
}